    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero" id="home">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <h1>AI that thinks <span class="emphasis">first.</span></h1>
            <p class="hero-text">Most AI generates words. We built a cognitive architecture designed to reason before it speaks. <strong>Aether</strong> is the reference implementation of the 8R architecture — a working model of what genuine machine cognition could look like.</p>
            <a href="#architecture" class="hero-cta">Explore the architecture</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROBLEM -->
    <section class="problem" id="problem">
        <div class="problem-grid">
            <h2>The problem</h2><br><h2>LLMs are impressive. Fluent. But not <span style="font-style:italic; color:var(--blue)">intelligent.</span></h2>
            <div class="problem-content">
                <div class="problem-item fade-in">
                    <h3>No understanding</h3>
                    <p>Today's systems generate text that sounds correct without modeling what the words mean, what goals they serve, or what consequences they will produce.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-item fade-in">
                    <h3>No memory of you</h3>
                    <p>Every conversation starts from zero. No true accumulation of understanding, no deepening relationship, no awareness.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-item fade-in">
                    <h3>No stable values</h3>
                    <p>Systems trained to please drift toward telling users what they want to hear. There is no mechanism to hold a position, resist pressure, or protect the person from bad advice.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FRAMEWORK -->
    <section id="architecture">
        <div class="framework">
            <div class="framework-left fade-in">
                <h2>The 8R Cognitive <span class="emphasis">Architecture</span></h2>
                <p class="subtitle">8R stands for Infinite ∞  Revision — our commitment to continuously re-examining our own thinking and applying it in our pursuit of building true, human-like artificial intelligence.</p>
                <p>Every AI model is built on an architecture. Most are built on the transformer — a prediction architecture whose job is to predict the next token. 8R is a different kind of architecture, designed around a different goal: genuine cognition.</p>
                <p>In the transformer paradigm, the language model is the brain. Words are generated to simulate reasoning. In 8R, reasoning is designed to happen first — in a structured cognitive space that models goals, tracks beliefs, weighs consequences, and holds values. The language model serves as a translation layer at the end, not the thinking itself.</p>
                <p>A model built on 8R is designed to think before it talks. To know what it knows and what it doesn't. To notice when something conflicts with its values before acting. To accumulate a persistent model of who you are — not just what you said in the last message.</p>
                <p>This is not a refinement of the existing paradigm. It is a different paradigm entirely — and Aether is our first attempt to build it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="framework-right">
                <div class="principle fade-in">
                    <h3>Meaning before language</h3>
                    <p>The architecture is designed to build a complete internal model of goals, beliefs, uncertainties, and values before any words are chosen. Language is output — not thought.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle fade-in">
                    <h3>Belief formation & revision</h3>
                    <p>Facts and beliefs are tracked separately, each with confidence scores and evidence counts. Contradictions are detected and resolved. The architecture is designed to know when it might be wrong.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle fade-in">
                    <h3>Causal reasoning</h3>
                    <p>The architecture models cause-and-effect relationships and evaluates consequences across multiple world models before acting — physical, social, psychological, economic, and technical perspectives synthesised into a single recommendation.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle fade-in">
                    <h3>Constitutional safety</h3>
                    <p>Six independent safety systems are designed to run on every cognitive cycle, woven into the execution graph itself. Every action must pass a constitutional gate before execution. There is no bypass path.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle fade-in">
                    <h3>Persistent identity</h3>
                    <p>Values and character are designed to be structurally stable. Drift dampening is built to resist being shaped — even over long interactions — into something value-inconsistent.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle fade-in">
                    <h3>Relationship memory</h3>
                    <p>Every interaction is stored and accumulated in persistent memory outside any context window. Trust is tracked asymmetrically. The architecture is designed so a model knows you differently over time than it did at the start.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle fade-in">
                    <h3>Intrinsic motivation</h3>
                    <p>The architecture maintains its own cognitive goals — coherence-seeking, uncertainty-reduction, exploration — designed to drive behaviour independent of user prompts.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- AETHER -->
    <section class="aether" id="aether">
        <div class="aether-header">
            <h2>Meet <span class="emphasis">Aether.</span></h2>
            <p>The reference implementation of the 8R architecture. Not a product — a proof of concept that the architecture works. Aether demonstrates that a cognitive model can be built that reasons before it speaks, accumulates genuine memory, and holds its values structurally rather than through instruction.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="aether-intro">
            <div class="fade-in">
                <p>Aether is what the 8R architecture looks like when fully implemented. It forms beliefs from conversation — not just responses. It is designed to track who you are: your trust level, your emotional tone, your values, your history — and build its model of you over time across sessions, stored in persistent memory rather than a context window.</p>
                <p>This distinction matters at the hardware level. A transformer-based model holds its conversational state as a KV cache in RAM — a small 7B model consumes 1–2 GB just to maintain an active context window, and that state resets to zero when the session ends. Aether's entire cognitive architecture initialises in approximately 8 MB. Accumulating 1,000 beliefs — the equivalent of months of interaction — adds less than 3 MB of RAM and under 400 KB on disk. The state persists. The cost stays flat.</p>
                <p>Its safety systems are not a content filter applied to output. Six constitutional systems are built into Aether's execution graph and designed to run on every cognitive cycle. Drift dampening is built to ensure the model resists being shaped into something value-inconsistent — though like all aspects of Aether, this has been verified in testing and continues to be refined.</p>
                <p>Language is the final layer. Belief formation, causal reasoning, consequence evaluation, constitutional validation — all of this is designed to happen inside Aether before any words are chosen. What reaches you is the translation of completed reasoning.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-grid fade-in">
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value">6</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Independent constitutional safety systems</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value">5</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">World model perspectives synthesised per decision</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value"><span class="emphasis">∞</span></div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Memory stored outside the context window — no expiration</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value">~<span class="emphasis">8</span>MB</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Total RAM for the full cognitive architecture — fixed overhead, benchmarked</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value">&lt;<span class="emphasis">3</span>KB</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">RAM per accumulated belief — 1,000 interactions costs less than 3 MB of state</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-value"><span class="emphasis">v1</span></div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Reference implementation — architecture proven, product development ongoing</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cap-grid">
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">01</div>
                <h3>Designed to remember you across time</h3>
                <p>Persistent episodic and semantic memory stored outside any context window. Aether is designed to track your trust level, emotional tone, values, and history — accumulating a model of you that grows with every session rather than resetting.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">02</div>
                <h3>Forms and revises beliefs</h3>
                <p>Concepts are stored with confidence scores and evidence counts. Contradictions are detected and resolved. It is designed to know when it might be wrong about you.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">03</div>
                <h3>Evaluates consequences before acting</h3>
                <p>Before acting, Aether evaluates outcomes across five world model perspectives — physical, social, psychological, economic, technical — synthesising them into a recommendation designed to reflect genuine understanding rather than probability.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">04</div>
                <h3>Built to hold values under pressure</h3>
                <p>Six constitutional systems gate every action. Drift dampening is designed to resist being shaped into something value-inconsistent over time. This is a structural property of the architecture — tested and continuing to be refined.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">05</div>
                <h3>Designed to notice patterns across time</h3>
                <p>The reflection engine is built to analyse episodic memory across sessions and adapt — without being asked. The architecture is designed so that Aether notices things about you that you haven't articulated, given sufficient interaction history.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">06</div>
                <h3>Acts with genuine curiosity</h3>
                <p>Seven intrinsic goals — coherence-seeking, uncertainty reduction, exploration — generate internal questions about gaps in understanding. Aether is designed to want to know, not just respond.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">07</div>
                <h3>Builds trust asymmetrically</h3>
                <p>Trust is earned, tracked, and calibrated. What Aether shares — and how directly — is designed to scale with accumulated trust. Relationships are intended to deepen because the memory is real.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">08</div>
                <h3>Agency loop — architecturally present</h3>
                <p>The architecture includes an agency loop designed to trigger cognitive cycles from internal goals and curiosity — not just user input. This capability is implemented in the reference architecture and is a priority for activation in future deployment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">09</div>
                <h3>Explains itself fully</h3>
                <p>Every cognitive cycle is designed to produce a complete audit record. Every blocked action is explainable. The reasoning chain behind any decision can be traced step by step — because the architecture requires it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cap-card fade-in">
                <div class="cap-num">10</div>
                <h3>Language model independence</h3>
                <p>The core cognitive architecture — belief formation, causal reasoning, constitutional validation — runs independently of any specific LLM. A rule-based language renderer is included as a fallback. Aether's cognition is not defined by the API that renders its words.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="revolution" id="capabilities">
        <div class="revolution-header fade-in">
            <h2>What this architecture is <span style="font-style:italic; color:var(--blue)">designed to enable.</span></h2>
            <p class="subtitle">The 8R architecture opens categories of application that prediction-based models are structurally unable to reach. These are not improvements on what current AI does — they are different things entirely, made possible by persistent memory, stable values, causal reasoning, and genuine consequence awareness working together.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="revolution-grid">
            <div class="rev-item fade-in">
                <h3>The first AI companion that <span class="emphasis">actually knows you</span></h3>
                <p>Not within a session — across months and years. One that is designed to notice when your mood has shifted since last week. That stores what you shared three months ago in persistent memory — not a context window. That builds a genuine, accumulating model of who you are. No prediction-based system is architecturally capable of this. 8R was built for it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rev-item fade-in">
                <h3>A wellness partner designed to <span class="emphasis">hold its position</span></h3>
                <p>Most AI companions drift toward telling users what they want to hear — because they are optimised to please. Drift dampening and identity attractors in the 8R architecture are designed to resist this — to hold a position even under sustained pressure. In wellness and coaching, a system that maintains honest care rather than drifting toward flattery isn't a feature — it's the entire product.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rev-item fade-in">
                <h3>High-stakes decisions with a <span class="emphasis">full audit trail</span></h3>
                <p>Every reasoning step recorded. Every blocked action explainable. Every belief traceable to the evidence that formed it. For clinical, legal, and financial applications where "the AI said so" is not acceptable — the 8R architecture produces the complete reasoning chain that institutions and regulators require, because reasoning and language are separated by design.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rev-item fade-in">
                <h3>Long-horizon coaching that <span class="emphasis">learns your patterns</span></h3>
                <p>A coach that tracks what you committed to, notices where you consistently fall short, and adapts based on what has actually worked with you specifically — not users in general. This requires genuine accumulating memory and active reflection across it. The 8R architecture is built for both.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rev-item fade-in">
                <h3>Autonomous agents that <span class="emphasis">are built to refuse</span></h3>
                <p>A model that can act in the world — browsing, writing, executing — but where the constitutional gate is structural, not instructed. The 8R architecture is designed so the safety cannot be argued away, flattered away, or prompt-engineered away. It is in the execution graph, not the system prompt.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rev-item fade-in">
                <h3>Multi-agent systems with <span class="emphasis">real social cognition</span></h3>
                <p>Multiple Aether instances, each managing a genuine relationship with one person on a team, sharing beliefs through a social graph. Theory of mind, trust dynamics, and collaborative goal tracking across models — built into the architecture from the start.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- COMPANION SECTION -->
    <section id="companion">
        <div class="companion">
            <div class="companion-left fade-in">
                <h2>A model designed to stay <span class="emphasis">itself.</span></h2>
                <p>The dream of a genuine AI companion — one with a consistent character, real memory of you, genuine curiosity, and the steadiness to be honest even when honesty is harder — has been out of reach. Not because it's impossible. Because no architecture was designed for it.</p>
                <p>The 8R architecture was. The things that define an unforgettable companion — unwavering loyalty, resistance to flattery, long memory, calm under pressure, stable character — are exactly the problems 8R was designed to solve at the architectural level. Aether is the first demonstration that this design works.</p>
                <p>A companion built on Aether is designed to know you over time the way a good friend does — to notice when something is off, to tell you the truth even when that's harder, and to remain the same model at the end of a long relationship. The architecture is built to hold that identity in place. It is early work. But the design is deliberate, and the foundation is real.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="companion-right fade-in">
                <div class="companion-trait">
                    <h3>Consistent character</h3>
                    <p>Identity attractor + drift dampening, built into the architecture. Designed to be the same model after 1,000 conversations as after the first.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="companion-trait">
                    <h3>Persistent memory</h3>
                    <p>Episodic memory stored outside any context window, with no expiration. Designed to accumulate a model of you that grows with every session.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="companion-trait">
                    <h3>Resistance to flattery</h3>
                    <p>Constitutional epistemic honesty enforced at the architectural level. Designed not to tell you what you want to hear at the expense of the truth.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="companion-trait">
                    <h3>Genuine curiosity</h3>
                    <p>Seven intrinsic curiosity goals built into the architecture generate internal questions about you. Designed to want to understand — not just respond.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="companion-trait">
                    <h3>Calm under pressure</h3>
                    <p>Coherence preservation and affect engine designed to maintain stable, grounded responses under adversarial or emotional pressure.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="companion-trait">
                    <h3>Earned trust</h3>
                    <p>Trust tracked asymmetrically and accumulated across every interaction. The relationship is designed to deepen over time — because the memory that enables it is real.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

